Seventeen short chapters, each of which describes the exploits and efforts of a unique, rather extraordinary individual. Each chapter shows how that person bucked normalcy and regular behavior into something unique and strange and broke away from some kind of existing system.

Break the rules, skip school, leave home, Move fast and break things. Stay hungry. Stay foolish. All that sort of thing.

The epilogue ends: "Don't ask. Build.

A fine read, quite quick, quite lively. The thing that's missing, of course, is all the people that do work in large organizations, who do collaborate who obey the rules.

It's very target-specific, mission-specific work.Hugely organized for what it wants to do.It's a book with a mission and a vision.

Having said that, it could use a bit of editing. There are sort of paragraphs and thoughts that are repeated Unnecessarily.

None-the-less, it's 24,000 highly organized words and thoughts.


